BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 157.20000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 1: Why Is the Sky Blue?) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Sunny loved asking questions about weather. Today she had a big one.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Mom, why is the sky blue? Why not green or purple or red?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Her mom smiled. 'That is a great science question! Let me show you.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (She held a glass prism in the sunlight and a rainbow appeared on the wall!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('Sunlight looks white, but it is actually made of ALL the colors mixed together!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('The sky is blue because of how those colors bounce around in the atmosphere.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: LIGHT SCATTERING) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Sunlight is made of all colors of the rainbow mixed together \(white light\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (When sunlight hits tiny gas molecules in the atmosphere, it bounces around \(scatters\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Blue light has a short wavelength, so it scatters much more than other colors.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (This scattered blue light reaches our eyes from every direction - making the sky look blue!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (At sunset, light travels through more atmosphere, scattering away all the blue,) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (leaving longer-wavelength red and orange light - that is why sunsets are red!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* The sky on Mars looks pinkish-red because of dust particles in its thin atmosphere.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* If Earth had no atmosphere, the sky would be black \(like on the Moon\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Violet light scatters even more than blue, but our eyes are more sensitive to blue.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Fill a glass with water, add a drop of milk, and shine a flashlight through it. See blue scattering!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why do you think the sky turns orange and red during sunset?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
