BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 147.6 720 Td (Chapter 3: Thunder and Lightning!) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (CRACK! BOOM! A thunderstorm rolled in one afternoon.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Sunny was not afraid - she was fascinated! She started counting.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('One-Mississippi, two-Mississippi, three...' BOOM! 'Three miles away!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('The lightning and thunder happen at the same time,' Sunny explained,) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('but light travels much faster than sound, so we see the flash first!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (She watched the incredible light show from the safety of her window.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: LIGHTNING & THUNDER) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Lightning is a giant spark of electricity between clouds or between a cloud and ground.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Inside storm clouds, ice particles collide and build up electrical charges.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Positive charges collect at the top, negative at the bottom, until ZAP - lightning!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Lightning is 5 times hotter than the surface of the Sun \(54,000 degrees F\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Thunder is the sound of air rapidly expanding from the extreme heat of lightning.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (Light travels at 186,000 miles/sec; sound at only 1,100 ft/sec. That is the delay!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* Earth gets struck by lightning about 100 times every second!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* Count seconds between flash and boom, divide by 5 = miles away.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Lightning can be up to 5 miles long and happen in under a millisecond.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Rub a balloon on your hair in the dark - see tiny sparks? That is static electricity like lightning!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why should you NEVER stand under a tree during a lightning storm?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
