BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 166.8 720 Td (Chapter 4: The Spinning Storm) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Sunny watched a documentary about the most powerful storms on Earth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Hurricanes are like giant spinning engines powered by warm ocean water!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (She learned that these massive storms can be 600 miles wide!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('And tornadoes are like nature's vacuum cleaners,' the narrator explained.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('They form when warm and cold air collide, creating a spinning vortex.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Sunny was amazed by nature's power, but also glad she knew how to stay safe.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: EXTREME STORMS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Hurricanes form over warm ocean water \(above 80F\) when moist air rises and spins.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (They can be 200-600 miles wide with winds over 157 mph \(Category 5\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (The calm center is called the 'eye' - it can be 20-40 miles across.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Tornadoes form when warm, moist air meets cold, dry air, creating rotation.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Tornado winds can reach 300 mph - the fastest winds on Earth!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 464 Td (SAFETY: Go to a basement or interior room. Stay away from windows!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 374 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 433 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 413 Td (* The US averages about 1,200 tornadoes per year \(most of any country\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 395 Td (* A hurricane releases energy equal to 10,000 nuclear bombs per day!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 377 Td (* Hurricanes in the Pacific are called 'typhoons'; in the Indian Ocean, 'cyclones.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 344 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 328 Td (Fill a bottle with water, flip it upside down, and swirl it - you made a vortex \(mini tornado\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 308 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 292 Td (Why do hurricanes weaken quickly after reaching land?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
