BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 181.2 720 Td (Chapter 5: Snowflake Magic) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Winter arrived and with it came Sunny's favorite weather event: SNOW!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (She caught a snowflake on her dark mitten and looked at it closely.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('It is a perfect six-pointed crystal!' she gasped. 'Like a tiny ice star!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Every single snowflake has six sides, but no two are exactly the same!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (She spent an hour catching and examining snowflakes, each one unique.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('Nature is the greatest artist,' Sunny decided, watching the world turn white.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: HOW SNOW FORMS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Snowflakes form when water vapor freezes directly into ice crystals in clouds.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (They always have six sides because of how water molecules bond together.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (As a crystal falls through the cloud, it grows arms and branches in unique patterns.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (The shape depends on temperature and humidity - that is why each one is different!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Fresh snow is actually about 90-95% air trapped between the crystals.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* The largest snowflake ever recorded was 15 inches wide \(Montana, 1887\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* It is NOT true that Eskimos have 50 words for snow \(but they do have several\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Snow appears white because light bounces off all the crystal surfaces.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Catch snowflakes on black paper or fabric and use a magnifying glass to see the crystals!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (If every snowflake is unique, how many different designs are possible?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
