BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 157.20000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 6: The Rainbow Surprise) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (After a spring rain shower, the sun came out and Sunny rushed outside.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('LOOK!' she shouted, pointing at the sky. A beautiful rainbow arched overhead!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet - all the colors in perfect order.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('A rainbow is like nature's prism!' Sunny explained to her little brother.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('Each raindrop acts like a tiny glass prism, splitting white light into colors!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('But you can only see it when the sun is behind you and rain is in front of you.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: LIGHT REFRACTION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (White sunlight is made up of all colors \(red, orange, yellow, green, blue, indigo, violet\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (When light enters a raindrop, it slows down and bends - this is called refraction.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Inside the drop, light reflects off the back surface like a mirror.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (As light exits the drop, it bends again, separating into all its colors!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (ROYGBIV helps you remember the rainbow color order.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* You can never reach the end of a rainbow - it moves as you move!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* From an airplane, you can see a full-circle rainbow \(not just an arch\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Double rainbows happen when light reflects twice inside each raindrop.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (On a sunny day, spray a garden hose with the sun behind you. Make your own rainbow!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why do the colors in a rainbow always appear in the same order?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
