BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 147.6 720 Td (Chapter 7: Why Do Seasons Change?) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td ('Why is it hot in summer and cold in winter?' Sunny wondered.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Is it because Earth is closer to the Sun in summer?' her friend guessed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('Actually, no!' Sunny had looked it up. 'It is because Earth is TILTED!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Our planet leans to one side at 23.5 degrees as it orbits the Sun.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('When our half tilts toward the Sun, we get more direct sunlight - that is summer!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('When it tilts away, sunlight hits at an angle - that is winter!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: EARTH'S TILT & SEASONS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Earth is tilted at 23.5 degrees on its axis \(like a leaning spinning top\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (As Earth orbits the Sun, different hemispheres tilt toward or away from the Sun.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (When the Northern Hemisphere tilts toward the Sun = summer in the north, winter in the south.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (When the Southern Hemisphere tilts toward the Sun = summer in the south, winter in the north.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (The equator gets direct sunlight year-round, which is why tropical areas are always warm.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* When it is summer in the US, it is winter in Australia \(and vice versa\)!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* The longest day \(summer solstice\) has about 15 hours of daylight.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* If Earth were NOT tilted, we would have no seasons - every day would be the same!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Shine a flashlight straight down on paper \(summer\), then at an angle \(winter\). Which is brighter?) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (If Earth were not tilted at all, what would life on our planet be like?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
