BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 166.8 720 Td (Chapter 8: Weather vs Climate) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td ('Sunny, are weather and climate the same thing?' asked her classmate.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Great question! They are related but different!' Sunny pulled out her notebook.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('Weather is what is happening RIGHT NOW outside - today's temperature and rain.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Climate is the pattern of weather over a LONG TIME - like 30 years or more.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('Think of it this way: weather is your mood today; climate is your personality!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('And just like personality can change slowly, our climate is changing too.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: WEATHER & CLIMATE) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Weather: short-term conditions \(today's temperature, humidity, wind, precipitation\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Climate: long-term average weather patterns in a region over 30+ years.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Climate change means Earth's average temperature is slowly rising over decades.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Greenhouse gases \(CO2, methane\) trap heat in the atmosphere like a blanket.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Everyone can help: use less energy, plant trees, reduce waste, bike more!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 72 449 Td (MORAL:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 13 Tf 72 431 Td (Understanding nature helps us protect our beautiful planet!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 342 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 401 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 381 Td (* Earth's average temperature has risen about 1.1C \(2F\) since 1880.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 363 Td (* Ice at the North and South Poles is melting faster each decade.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 345 Td (* One tree can absorb about 48 pounds of CO2 per year. Plant more trees!) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
